August 10 at 2:30 AM ·

As part of our Fall Sports Kickoff at Kinkaider Brewing on Tuesday, we will be auctioning off the Suite Box Seating for the football game against St Paul. These suites will be auctioned off in a combination online and live auction.

1. We will open the auction online tomorrow (Monday, August 10th) at 5PM and it will close after 24 hours.
2. The final online bids (at 5PM on Tuesday, August 11th) will be the opening bids for the live auction.
3. The live auction portion will occur on Tuesday night around 7PM at Kinkaider.

Adams Land & Cattle
May 22 at 1:24 AM ·

After almost 30 years of welcoming 3rd graders to our operations, we didn’t want this to be the first year they couldn’t make it on the lot!

So, last week, we continued our tradition of sharing our knowledge of #cattlefeeding by giving a virtual tour with approximately 50 students! To help us, we enlisted the 3rd grade sons and daughters of our employees to share some facts with their friends.

A huge thanks to North Park Elementary School and the third grade teachers for allowing us to connect agriculture in the classrooms!

post_text:
Parents of 6th - 11th Grade Students:

Thursday, May 14th will be the last day of school for the 2019-2020 school year. On that day we will open the school from 7:30 am - 4:00 pm to have ALL MIDDLE SCHOOL AND HIGH SCHOOL STUDENTS return any library books, textbooks, school supplies, Chromebook, case, and charger that they have or pay any fees. Students need to enter through the Library West small door. They will return their Chromebook in the Media Center. There will be designated tables for each grade to return school supplies and checkout. High School tables will be in the Media Center and Middle School tables will be in front of the High School office. When students are finished checking out they will walk out double doors by the flagpole or doors by the band room. If your student is ill please call the school to arrange to pick up. All students must obey social distancing rules and please no group gathering.

text:
Parents of 6th - 11th Grade Students:

Thursday, May 14th will be the last day of school for the 2019-2020 school year. On that day we will open the school from 7:30 am - 4:00 pm to have ALL MIDDLE SCHOOL AND HIGH SCHOOL STUDENTS return any library books, textbooks, school supplies, Chromebook, case, and charger that they have or pay any fees. Students need to enter through the Library West small door. They will return their Chromebook in the Media Center. There will be designated tables for each grade to return school supplies and checkout. High School tables will be in the Media Center and Middle School tables will be in front of the High School office. When students are finished checking out they will walk out double doors by the flagpole or doors by the band room. If your student is ill please call the school to arrange to pick up. All students must obey social distancing rules and please no group gathering.

Thanks and any questions please contact the High School office.

Broken Bow YLCC Earth Week
April 20 at 7:21 PM ·

Hello everyone! We are Broken Bow students part of Youth Leadership Custer County. Our organization focuses on high school upperclassmen improving leadership skills, diversifying, utilizing their communication skills, and promoting community improvement. We meet once a month to learn new things, make connections with each other, and work on making the world around us a better place. For our community improvement project, we decided to celebrate Earth Day. We’re taking it one step further though, and educating people throughout the whole week to make an EARTH WEEK! We originally had many ideas to do activities to help the planet through our school, but because of the current situation, we decided to take it virtual and promote others to do the same! The week of Earth Week (April 20th-24th) we are posting challenges on our Facebook page that will challenge you to do something to better the Earth in our community. We can all improve our community by celebrating Earth Day and Earth Week with us! We hope you like our everyday challenges and celebrate with us!

post_text:
UPDATE FROM NSAA:

As a follow up to the information that we sent out this past week about the Pre-Participation Physical Exams (PPE), I have received several emails asking for clarification regarding 7th & 8th Grade PPEs. So, I wanted to make sure that everyone was receiving the same response.

The requirement for students entering the7th grade to have a physical exam is Nebraska state education law and we do not have the ability to waive that requirement. However, the physicals that the current 7th graders have for the 2019-2020 school year can be used for NSAA purposes for the 2020-2021 school year.

After discussions with legal counsel and our insurance provider, due to our catastrophic insurance requirements, all current 8th Grade students that are going to enter the 9th grade in 2020, will STILL be required to get a PPE for the 2020-2021 school year. All other high school students entering grades 10, 11 & 12 grades that have a PPE paperwork for 2019-2020 school year, can use that physical for the 2020-2021 school year.

post_text:
WINTER SPORTS BANQUET

The Broken Bow Athletic Booster Club will host the Annual Winter Sports Banquet on TUESDAY, March 17, 2020 at the One Box Convention Center beginning at 6:30 p.m. The
Banquet will honor all 9-12 grade winter athletes, including participants in Girls’ and Boys’ Basketball, Wrestling, and Cheerleading. All students and their families who participated in a winter sport are encouraged to attend. Each family is asked to bring a main dish. If your last name begins with A-L, you should also bring a dessert. If your last name begins with M-Z, you should also bring a salad. Please bring your own serving utensils. Table settings and beverages will be provided.

THANK YOU,
BROKEN BOW ATHLETIC BOOSTER CLUB
